		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm almost sure, but I still need to be absolutely sure:
<br />
<br />if we say that the NES can only display 25 colors on a screen, is it explained by this:
<br />
<br />12*2 + 1 =25
<br />
<br />which is, the number of different colors on backgroud palette and sprite palette + the background color? ( because palettes hold 16 colors but 4 entries in each palette are overiden by the background color)
<br />
<br />Is this exact?

		

